  "description": [
    "PAGE TWO The Montgomery County Sentinel Published Every Thursday at Rockville Md P G Stromberg Publisher Leslie H Peard Baltimore Advertising Representative 918 Balto Life Bldg Baltimore Md Telephone MUlberry 3134 SubscriptionOne Dollar per year in advance Entered at the Post Office at Rockville Md as second class matter THURSDAY NOVEMBER 19 1942 Army Trained And Equipped The strength of the U S Army has passed 4500 000 men and more than 800000 soldiers have been safely transported overseas This achievement dwarfs any similar accomplish ment in the first World War but it is even more encour aging when we consider that the arms equipment and supplies of the present American army are for the most part the products of oup own war industries In the earlier World War much of the arms and materiel used by American troops was provided by the British and French In this war we are not only train ing a vast Army but we are also providing it with the tools of war Reports from various battlegrounds indi cate that the tools are unexcelled by those of any other army V Who Has Headquarters Every once in a while we note dispatch from Gen"
  ],
